org.locationtech.geowave.core.index.dimension

Class UnboundedDimensionDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.locationtech.geowave.core.index.dimension.BasicDimensionDefinition
      • org.locationtech.geowave.core.index.dimension.UnboundedDimensionDefinition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NumericDimensionDefinition, Persistable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CustomCRSUnboundedSpatialDimension, CustomCRSUnboundedSpatialDimensionX, CustomCRSUnboundedSpatialDimensionY, TimeDefinition

    public class UnboundedDimensionDefinition
extends BasicDimensionDefinition
    Because space filling curves require an extent (minimum & maximum), the unbounded implementation relies on an external binning strategy to translate an unbounded variable into bounded bins
